    "caption": "Standing completely still at the water's edge, like a statue with patience.",
    "shortDescription": "Herons are ambush hunters — they stand in shallow water without moving for so long that fish forget they're there, then strike with a lightning-fast stab of their dagger bill. They can stand on one leg in a stream for thirty minutes without twitching. Fun fact: Herons have special neck vertebrae that let them fold their neck into a tight S-shape for a faster, more powerful strike."
